<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News]]></title><link/> https://sputniknews.com/新闻<atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/sputniknews" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RSSHub</generator><webmaster> i@diygod.me (DIY神)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 5 月 17 日星期三 01:09:33 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[US Dollar's Time as Top Currency 'Coming to An End' - Investor]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110409965" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/106730/72/1067307231_0:0:2825:2298_1440x900_80_0_1_b6fd79765d221f6a61ebe8229af6b12f.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1067307230" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/us-dollars-time-as-top-currency-coming-to-an-end---investor-1110409965.html?share-img=1067307230"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / LM Otero /</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">得克萨斯州沃思堡雕刻和印刷局西部货币设施中的一叠 100 美元钞票</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="Stacks of $100 bills at the Bureau of Engraving and Printing Western Currency Facility in Fort Worth, Texas - Sputnik International, 1920, 17.05.2023" title="在得克萨斯州沃思堡的雕刻和印刷局西方货币设施中成堆的 100 美元钞票" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/106730/72/1067307231_0:355:2825:1944_1920x0_80_0_0_64d4ad3f1c78c48caf2b8751448bf83d.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/106730/72/1067307231_0:355:2825:1944_640x0_80_0_0_253a5af142ab8f1591f5e4079876736a.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/106730/72/1067307231_0:355:2825:1944_1280x0_80_0_0_9687be496d67125308e58102d2d980ee.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/106730/72/1067307231_0:355:2825:1944_1920x0_80_0_0_64d4ad3f1c78c48caf2b8751448bf83d.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © AP Photo / LM Otero / </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据华盛顿（人造卫星）网报道：美国著名投资者吉姆·罗杰斯告诉人造卫星网：由于华盛顿缺乏中立性和对美国信誉的担忧，美元作为世界最大货币的时代即将结束。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">罗杰斯说：“美国的许多朋友都在行动，试图找到可以与美元竞争并最终取代美元的东西。” </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “它会发生的。它一直在发生。美国的时代即将结束。这次美元即将结束。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110409965" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/us-dollars-time-as-top-currency-coming-to-an-end---investor-1110409965.html?share-block=1110409967" data-title="&quot;It will happen. It has always happened. And America's time is coming to an end. The American dollar this time is coming to an end.&quot; "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “150 多年来，没有一种货币处于领先地位。没有人一直处于领先地位，所以它总是发生，”罗杰斯说。 “人们已经远离任何货币。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">罗杰斯指出，这些国家现在正在远离美元，部分原因是美国是世界历史上最大的债务国。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “很多人开始说：等一下，我不知道我们是否要用这笔钱，因为总有一天会出问题，”他说。 “而且，世界国际货币应该是完全中性的。任何人都可以用它来做任何你想做的事情。但现在华盛顿正在改变规则。如果他们对你生气，他们就会切断你的联系。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110409965" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/us-dollars-time-as-top-currency-coming-to-an-end---investor-1110409965.html?share-block=1110409970" data-title="&quot;Many people are starting to say: wait a minute, I don't know if we want to use that money, because it will have a problem someday,&quot; he said. &quot;But also, the world’s international currency is supposed to be completely neutral. Anybody can use it for anything you want. But now Washington is changing the rules. And if they get angry at you, they cut you off. "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">他补充说，美国对俄罗斯的制裁正在加速人们寻找与美元竞争的东西的步伐。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “即使是美国的朋友也担心他们会发生什么事。因此世界的发展速度越来越快，”他说。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110409965" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/us-dollars-time-as-top-currency-coming-to-an-end---investor-1110409965.html?share-block=1110409972" data-title="&quot;Even America’s friends are worried that something could happen to them. And so the world is moving more rapidly,&quot; he said. "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">近几个月来，俄罗斯一直在加强与中国的经济合作，并采用人民币进行贸易。 4 月初，人民币取代美元成为俄罗斯交易量最大的货币，中国货币继续渗透到世界其他许多市场。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h2"><h2 class="article__h2">世界尚未找到替代美元甚至与美元竞争的货币</h2></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这位知名投资者进一步指出，各国正在努力摆脱美元，但还没有一种货币可以替代或至少与之竞争。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “到目前为止，世界还没有找到可以替代甚至与美元竞争的东西，”罗杰斯说。 “中国货币，你肯定会想，但中国人不让你买卖货币，它没有完全转换......美国的许多朋友正在行动，试图找到与美国竞争并最终取代美国的东西美元。它会发生的。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110409965" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/us-dollars-time-as-top-currency-coming-to-an-end---investor-1110409965.html?share-block=1110409977" data-title="&quot;So far, the world hasn't found something to replace or even compete with the dollar,&quot; Rogers said. &quot;The Chinese currency, sure you would think, but the Chinese don't let you buy and sell the currency, it’s not completely converted ... Many friends of America are moving, trying to find something to compete with and ultimately replace the US dollar. It will happen.&quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 5 月初，国际货币基金组织总裁克里斯塔利娜·格奥尔基耶娃 (Kristalina Georgieva) 表示，尽管越来越多的国家开始在贸易中转向本国货币，但她认为在不久的将来不会有替代美元的选择。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">罗杰斯说：“是的，世界正试图加速远离美元，显然大国在这方面的影响力更大，也更有理由比其他国家更快地做到这一点。” </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “因此，许多国家……正在努力弄清楚我们该怎么做才能找到替代美元或与美元竞争的东西。” </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110409965" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/us-dollars-time-as-top-currency-coming-to-an-end---investor-1110409965.html?share-block=1110409981" data-title="&amp;quot;So, many countries... are trying to figure out what do we do to find something to replace the US dollar, or to compete with the US dollar.&amp;quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 4 月，国际货币基金组织表示，美元自 2022 年 10 月以来一直在贬值，但仍比 2000 年以来的强势。同月，世界银行行长戴维·马尔帕斯表示，美元的主导地位受到诸如区块链技术和人民币。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 17 May 2023 01:04:57 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/us-dollars-time-as-top-currency-coming-to-an-end---investor-1110409965.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/us-dollars-time-as-top-currency-coming-to-an-end---investor-1110409965.html<category>经济</category><category>吉姆罗杰斯</category><category>华盛顿</category><category>世界银行</category><category>中国</category><category>倾销美元</category><category>放弃美元</category><category>货币</category><category>储备货币</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[TLDR: Too Long, Didn't Russia?]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110409612" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/10/1110408186_0:0:2000:1500_1440x900_80_0_1_55261e5c6365467d00702c0627437adc.jpg?source-sid=rian_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1110408168" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/tldr-too-long-didnt-russia-1110409612.html?share-img=1110408168"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Sputnik / Ted Rall</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">没有勾结</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="rian_photo" alt="No Collusion - Sputnik International, 1920, 17.05.2023" title="无勾结" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/10/1110408186_0:0:2000:1125_1920x0_80_0_0_bff9c15543dc989d32de3673f8348a31.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/10/1110408186_0:0:2000:1125_640x0_80_0_0_5dce37fddb52bd6658e9f1bb6bf37001.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/10/1110408186_0:0:2000:1125_1280x0_80_0_0_21bc65386d30db34c124b777ea44d498.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/10/1110408186_0:0:2000:1125_1920x0_80_0_0_bff9c15543dc989d32de3673f8348a31.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © Sputnik / 泰德·拉尔</div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">自特朗普 2016 年当选以来，甚至更早之前，民主党人及其最坚定的支持者就曾提出未经证实的说法，称俄罗斯与特朗普勾结，帮助他击败希拉里克林顿并获得总统职位。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">所谓勾结的证据一开始充其量是站不住脚的，但这并没有阻止民主党人重复这种令人作呕的说法。即使在穆勒报告没有发现前美国总统唐纳德特朗普与俄罗斯勾结的证据之后，他们仍继续提出索赔。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">约翰·达勒姆 (John Durham) 周一发布的<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230516/durham-report-what-is-known-so-far-1110402005.html" target="_blank">报告</a>更进一步，称没有足够的证据需要进行全面调查，并指责联邦调查局<strong>“低估或故意忽视重要信息”，这与特朗普和俄罗斯勾结的说法形成鲜明对比。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">达勒姆还指责联邦调查局使用“原始、未经分析和未经证实的情报”展开调查，并在考虑克林顿竞选活动干预选举的指控时使用了不同的标准。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">该报告得出结论，“[司法]部和联邦调查局未能履行其在[达勒姆]报告中描述的某些事件和活动中严格遵守法律的重要使命。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110409612" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/tldr-too-long-didnt-russia-1110409612.html?share-block=1110409616" data-title="The report concludes “that the [Justice] Department and FBI failed to uphold their important mission of strict fidelity to the law in connection with certain events and activities described in [Durham’s] report.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">尽管有这份报告，以及之前的穆勒报告，民主党盟友<a href="https://twitter.com/WalshFreedom/status/1658282757263425536" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">继续声称</a>有勾结的证据。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 17 May 2023 00:33:09 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/tldr-too-long-didnt-russia-1110409612.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/tldr-too-long-didnt-russia-1110409612.html<category>美洲</category><category>唐纳德·特朗普</category><category>希拉里·克林顿</category><category>罗伯特·穆勒</category><category>达勒姆</category><category>联邦调查局</category><category>民主党人</category><category>俄罗斯</category><category>泰德拉尔</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Biden Quietly Ends Trump-Era Policy Blocking Foreign Gov Funding of US Think Tanks]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110408708" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/19/1109815168_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_0724354ff34a67ca1ed561f84c6b0e2d.jpg?source-sid=afp" data-photoview-image-id="1109815150" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230516/biden-quietly-ends-trump-era-policy-blocking-foreign-gov-funding-of-us-think-tanks-1110408708.html?share-img=1109815150"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / SAUL LOEB</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">美国总统乔·拜登于 2022 年 11 月 5 日在伊利诺伊州乔利埃特的琼斯小学就降低处方药成本以及保护社会保障和医疗保险发表讲话。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="afp" alt="US President Joe Biden speaks about lowering prescription drug costs and protecting Social Security and Medicare at Jones Elementary School in Joliet, Illinois, November 5, 2022. - Sputnik International, 1920, 16.05.2023" title="2022 年 11 月 5 日，美国总统乔·拜登在伊利诺伊州乔利埃特的琼斯小学谈到降低处方药成本并保护社会保障和医疗保险。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/19/1109815168_0:0:3072:1728_1920x0_80_0_0_eef7c563a82093e68044c6f28d6eae74.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/19/1109815168_0:0:3072:1728_640x0_80_0_0_6cb7b96b25b643a2084b15c556eac2fd.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/19/1109815168_0:0:3072:1728_1280x0_80_0_0_c0b6591c916ab0a6d1bd096a048ed3e4.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/19/1109815168_0:0:3072:1728_1920x0_80_0_0_eef7c563a82093e68044c6f28d6eae74.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / SAUL LOEB </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">伊恩德马蒂诺</div><div class="article__author-links"> <a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_demartino_ian/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">拜登政府领导下的美国国务院悄然结束了特朗普时代的一项政策，该政策要求智库披露外国政府和外国政府拥有的组织的捐赠。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这一变化最先由凯西·米歇尔 (Casey Michel) 在《新共和国》( <a href="https://newrepublic.com/article/172523/think-tanks-foreign-money-transparency" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">The New Republic)</a>中报道，但美国主流媒体却忽略了这一变化，尽管它让美国政府可以接受来自各国（包括独裁国家和有时是敌对国家）的秘密外国影响活动。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">智库在美国政治中发挥着重要作用，尤其是在外交政策方面。当迈克·庞培 (Mike Pompeo) 领导的国务院在 2020 年取缔这些资金时，他特别指出了它们在外交政策中的作用，以此作为该规则的正当理由。 <strong>“智库在处理外交事务中的独特作用使得外国资金的透明度比以往任何时候都更加重要，”他说。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">与外国游说者不同，智库成员不受《外国代理人登记法》的约束，这使他们成为外国实体的有吸引力的目标，这些实体打算在不暴露的情况下影响美国政策。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">特朗普时代的规则为智库的阴暗世界带来了一些清晰度，但在没有解释或宣布的情况下，安东尼布林肯领导的国务院取消了该政策，再次允许外国实体资助美国强大的智库没有一点透明度。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>独立调查记者克里斯托弗·赫拉利 (Christopher Helali) 周一对人造卫星电台 (Radio Sputnik) 的 Political Misfits 表示：“我们看到的是，由于缺乏透明度，一些政府可能不想公开自己的所作所为以及资助的原因，从而产生黑钱。”</strong> . </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “这些智囊团在塑造话语方面发挥着重要作用。所以如果你能安全地隐瞒这笔钱的来源，你就不必对任何人负责。如果这个政府侵犯人权，政府也不必回答他们为什么要捐钱，这些钱从哪里来。” </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110408708" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230516/biden-quietly-ends-trump-era-policy-blocking-foreign-gov-funding-of-us-think-tanks-1110408708.html?share-block=1110408714" data-title="“These think tanks serve an important role in shaping the discourse. So if you can safely conceal where that money is coming from, you don’t have to answer to anybody. Neither do governments have to answer why they are giving money, where this money is coming from, if this government has human rights violations.&amp;quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">值得注意的是，以乔·拜登总统命名的智库宾夕法尼亚拜登中心在宣布成立后被认定向宾夕法尼亚州立大学赠送了数百万美元的资金后，被指收受了中国的捐款。宾夕法尼亚拜登中心的 DC 办公室是去年发现拜登担任副总统期间的机密文件的地方。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>根据米歇尔的说法，在人权方面有着令人担忧或不容置疑的不良记录的政府一直在资助美国的智库，包括阿塞拜疆、哈萨克斯坦、卡塔尔和阿拉伯联合酋长国 (UAE)。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">阿联酋尤其活跃，由于披露要求的短暂性，据透露，阿联酋政府是美国智库的最大单一外国捐助者，击败了民主盟友瑞典和英国。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>根据全球人类自由指数，阿联酋在 165 个国家中个人自由排名第 153 位，每年向包括大西洋理事会、阿斯彭研究所、布鲁金斯学会、美国进步中心在内的知名智库捐赠数百万美元和中东研究所。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">就大西洋理事会而言，阿联酋至少是第二大外国捐助者。虽然它没有透露该国捐赠了多少，但这足以使其跻身最高捐助者行列，这是仅有的两个达到这一数字的外国之一，另一个是英国。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">黎巴嫩前总理拉菲克·哈里里之子、亿万富翁商人巴哈·哈里里也被列为头号捐助者。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “当然，”赫拉利告诉人造卫星网，“他们是在为影响力和自己的地位提供资金。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110408708" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230516/biden-quietly-ends-trump-era-policy-blocking-foreign-gov-funding-of-us-think-tanks-1110408708.html?share-block=1110408722" data-title="“Of course,” Helali told Sputnik, “they were funding for influence and their own position.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">今年早些时候，大西洋理事会主席弗雷德里克·肯佩 (Frederick Kempe) 在美国一家主要媒体发表了一篇文章，称赞阿联酋选择在今年晚些时候主办第 28 届联合国气候变化会议，这笔资金得到了回报。大西洋理事会与阿联酋之间的联系在出版时并未披露。该媒体后来添加了一份公开的编辑说明，并指出 Kempe 最初并未向他们透露这种联系。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">但大西洋理事会成员和其他智库成员的数十篇文章每年都会在主要媒体上发表。他们经常主张美国政府采取外交政策行动，包括在<u><a href="https://thehill.com/opinion/national-security/3508456-36-experts-agree-stay-the-course-in-ukraine/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">乌克兰</a></u>、 <u><a href="https://thehill.com/opinion/international/548682-afghanistan-an-impossible-choice/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">阿富汗</a></u>、 <u><a href="https://thehill.com/opinion/national-security/3907622-20-years-on-shock-and-awe-remains-relevant/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">伊拉克</a></u>和<u><a href="https://www.washingtonexaminer.com/news/your-god-is-xi-jinping-uighurs-mocked-and-tortured-in-chinese-internment-camps-for-their-faith" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">中国</a></u>等问题上。这些专栏文章由名义上的自由派和保守派媒体发表，他们与他们的智库的联系很少被披露，文章中对所述智库的资金披露更是罕见。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Facebook* 还委托大西洋理事会帮助“打击选举宣传”。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “这是一个非常黑暗的日子，当你失去透明度并且你最终没有意识到幕后发生的事情时，”Helali 说。 “这是特朗普政府所做的唯一进步的事情之一，遗憾的是我们已经失去了它。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110408708" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230516/biden-quietly-ends-trump-era-policy-blocking-foreign-gov-funding-of-us-think-tanks-1110408708.html?share-block=1110408726" data-title="“It is a very dark day when you lose transparency and you end up not realizing what is going on behind the scenes,” says Helali. “This was one of the only progressive things the Trump administration did and sadly we’ve lost it.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">国务院和白宫尚未对取消的政策发表评论。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> <em>*Facebook 及其母公司 Meta 在俄罗斯因极端主义活动而被禁止。</em></div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 16 May 2023 23:59:30 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230516/biden-quietly-ends-trump-era-policy-blocking-foreign-gov-funding-of-us-think-tanks-1110408708.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230516/biden-quietly-ends-trump-era-policy-blocking-foreign-gov-funding-of-us-think-tanks-1110408708.html<category>分析</category><category>阿联酋</category><category>乔·拜登</category><category>唐纳德·特朗普</category><category>弗雷德里克·肯普</category><category>大西洋理事会</category><category>外国代理人登记法 (FARA)</category><category>白色的房子</category><category>人造卫星</category><category>国务院</category><category>安东尼布林肯</category><category>迈克·蓬佩奥</category><category>2018 外国影响透明度法案</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[UN on Ukraine Intel Chief Admitting to Assassinations in Russia: We're Against Terror Acts]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110408955" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/07/0a/1083353164_0:0:2366:1577_1440x900_80_0_1_e289815a8d0e3aa26395b8367f13f35d.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1083353162" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230516/un-on-ukraine-intel-chief-admitting-to-assassinations-in-russia-were-against-terror-acts-1110408955.html?share-img=1083353162"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Adam Rountree</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">在这张 2005 年 9 月 13 日的档案照片中，会员国的国旗在纽约联合国总部的大会大楼外飘扬。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="In this Sept. 13, 2005, file photo, the flags of member nations fly outside the General Assembly building at the United Nations headquarters in New York. - Sputnik International, 1920, 16.05.2023" title="在这张 2005 年 9 月 13 日的档案照片中，成员国的国旗在纽约联合国总部的大会大楼外飘扬。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/07/0a/1083353164_0:123:2367:1454_1920x0_80_0_0_f737657aeb0f3247f1acb3025a8ed9ad.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/07/0a/1083353164_0:123:2367:1454_640x0_80_0_0_5b443f636cd57ef871c0e115dfde661b.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/07/0a/1083353164_0:123:2367:1454_1280x0_80_0_0_968276ee0e057e54e2ca4fe1704fd034.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/07/0a/1083353164_0:123:2367:1454_1920x0_80_0_0_f737657aeb0f3247f1acb3025a8ed9ad.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Adam Rountree </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据联合国（人造卫星）网报道：联合国周二表示，没有看到乌克兰军事情报局局长基里洛·布达诺夫声称对俄罗斯最近暗杀公众人物事件负责的言论，但反对“所有”恐怖袭击。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “我没有看到这句话。我无法谈论它的真实性，”发言人斯蒂芬·杜加里克在一次简报会上说。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “但当然，我们反对任何和所有恐怖主义行为。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110408955" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230516/un-on-ukraine-intel-chief-admitting-to-assassinations-in-russia-were-against-terror-acts-1110408955.html?share-block=1110408957" data-title="&quot;But of course, we stand against any and all acts of terrorism.&quot; "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在周二发布的 YouTube 采访中，布达诺夫承认基辅参与了最近对俄罗斯公众人物的暗杀，并吹嘘说乌克兰已经“搞定”了其中的许多人。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">与此同时，布达诺夫拒绝透露乌克兰是否是本月早些时候谋杀俄罗斯作家、政治家和政党“公正的俄罗斯——为了真相”联合主席扎哈尔·普里莱平 (Zakhar Prilepin) 未遂的幕后黑手。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “当你涉及到个人问题时，我必须像世界上任何情报部门通常做的那样回答你。我们不能对这种情况发表评论，也不能确认或否认这些信息，”这位情报官员补充说。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p> 5月6日，普里列平的汽车在俄罗斯下诺夫哥罗德州的高速公路上被炸毁。司机当场死亡，Prilepin 受伤。当天晚些时候，地区警方在紧追不舍的情况下逮捕了这起暗杀行动的主要嫌疑人亚历山大·佩尔米亚科夫 (Alexander Permyakov)。</p><p>俄罗斯调查委员会称，他在接受审讯时承认，他是按照乌克兰特种部队的指示行事的。</p></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">另一起涉及俄罗斯知名人士的恐怖袭击发生在 4 月初。一个身份不明的爆炸装置在圣彼得堡市中心的一家咖啡馆爆炸，炸死了军事记者弗拉德伦·塔塔尔斯基。俄罗斯国家反恐委员会表示，恐怖袭击是由乌克兰特种部队策划的。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在本月早些时候接受美国媒体采访时，布达诺夫 - 当被问及据报道美国情报部门将 8 月汽车炸弹暗杀 Daria Dugina 归因于乌克兰政府时 - 要求不要“继续那个话题”。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">相反，他补充说，他只会评论乌克兰军队“一直在杀害俄罗斯人”，并且“将继续在这个世界的任何地方杀害俄罗斯人，直到乌克兰取得完全胜利”。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p>当时，克里姆林宫发言人德米特里佩斯科夫表示，布达诺夫的声明证实俄罗斯总统弗拉基米尔普京在乌克兰开始特别军事行动是正确的。</p><p>佩斯科夫说，布达诺夫的“骇人听闻”的话直接证实了乌克兰当局“不仅是恐怖活动的支持者，还是恐怖活动的组织者”。</p></div></div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 16 May 2023 23:29:22 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230516/un-on-ukraine-intel-chief-admitting-to-assassinations-in-russia-were-against-terror-acts-1110408955.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230516/un-on-ukraine-intel-chief-admitting-to-assassinations-in-russia-were-against-terror-acts-1110408955.html<category>世界</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>基辅</category><category>俄罗斯</category><category>联合国 (UN)</category><category> YouTube</category><category>斯蒂芬·杜加里克</category><category>扎哈尔普里平</category><category>暗杀</category><category>有针对性的杀戮</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Secret Service Probing How Unidentified Man Entered US National Security Adviser's Home]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110407273" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/12/1109634428_0:0:3015:2011_1440x900_80_0_1_ecd9a473849729d50bbd6bf6dd0d984c.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1109634410" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230516/secret-service-probing-how-unidentified-man-entered-us-national-security-advisers-home-1110407273.html?share-img=1109634410"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Nancy Benac</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">2023 年 4 月 18 日，星期二，美国特勤局穿制服的警察带着一个小孩爬过华盛顿宾夕法尼亚大道的白宫围栏。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="U.S. Secret Service uniformed division police officers carry a young child who crawled through the White House fence on Pennsylvania Avenue in Washington, Tuesday, April 18, 2023.  - Sputnik International, 1920, 16.05.2023" title="2023 年 4 月 18 日，星期二，美国特勤局穿制服的警察带着一个小孩爬过华盛顿宾夕法尼亚大道的白宫围栏。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/12/1109634428_0:0:3015:1697_1920x0_80_0_0_084e5ffd18c8f7649ae7b8c5306d6ce0.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/12/1109634428_0:0:3015:1697_640x0_80_0_0_cfd1658d05494d47257f0a2adbc18a9b.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/12/1109634428_0:0:3015:1697_1280x0_80_0_0_1e1c61f3a048d01f86063781af09caf9.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/12/1109634428_0:0:3015:1697_1920x0_80_0_0_084e5ffd18c8f7649ae7b8c5306d6ce0.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片/南希贝纳克</div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据华盛顿（人造卫星）网报道：美国媒体周二援引知情人士的话报道称，美国特勤局正在调查一名身份不明的男子如何在未被其安保人员发现的情况下进入美国国家安全顾问杰克沙利文的家中。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">报告称，闯入者似乎喝醉了，不知道自己身在何处，而且没有证据表明闯入者认识沙利文或打算伤害他。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">针对此事，美国特勤局（USSS）告诉人造卫星，它正在调查发生在“受保护地点”的安全事件，并对事件展开全面调查。美国海军证实受保护者没有受到伤害。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>作为一项预防措施，特勤局在调查进行期间对沙利文及其住所实施了额外的安全预防措施。白宫拒绝就此事发表评论。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">去年 10 月，一名入侵者闯入南希·佩洛西<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20221028/pelosis-husband-assaulted-as-result-of-house-attack-1102800093.html" target="_blank">(Nancy Pelosi) 在旧金山的家中并袭击了她的丈夫</a>，大声呼喊当时的众议院议长的下落。佩洛西在袭击期间不在家，但这一事件凸显了政客的安全漏洞。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">近年来，由于受其保护的人员名单不断扩大和资金不足，特勤局面临着挑战。该机构的预算无法跟上增加的责任，因为受其保护的人数从 2000 年的 18 人大幅增加到目前的 27 人。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 16 May 2023 22:57:13 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230516/secret-service-probing-how-unidentified-man-entered-us-national-security-advisers-home-1110407273.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230516/secret-service-probing-how-unidentified-man-entered-us-national-security-advisers-home-1110407273.html<category>美洲</category><category>我们</category><category>杰克沙利文</category><category>美国特勤局</category><category>南希·佩洛西</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Turkiye Will Continue to Walk Tightrope Between West and East if Kilicdaroglu Wins]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110405544" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/13/1109671580_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_868ef86fa2bb3f484608dd1bfcc03692.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1109671562" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230516/turkiye-will-continue-to-walk-tightrope-between-west-and-east-if-kilicdaroglu-wins-1110405544.html?share-img=1109671562"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Francisco Seco</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">2023 年 4 月 18 日，星期二，土耳其伊斯坦布尔，人们走过印有土耳其 CHP 党领袖和国家联盟总统候选人 Kemal Kilicdaroglu 照片的横幅。土耳其总统选举定于 5 月 14 日举行。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="People walk past banners with the photograph of Turkish CHP party leader and Nation Alliance's presidential candidate Kemal Kilicdaroglu in Istanbul, Turkey, Tuesday, April 18, 2023. Presidential elections in Turkey are scheduled to take place on May 14.  - Sputnik International, 1920, 16.05.2023" title="2023 年 4 月 18 日，星期二，土耳其伊斯坦布尔，人们走过带有土耳其 CHP 党领袖和国家联盟总统候选人凯末尔·基利达罗格鲁照片的横幅。土耳其总统选举定于 5 月 14 日举行。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/13/1109671580_0:160:3072:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_23690fe7a9469f27a077a58657b30863.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/13/1109671580_0:160:3072:1888_640x0_80_0_0_b8db73baa260e318ef5cb2c69a871c7f.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/13/1109671580_0:160:3072:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_c9623abddf1c83e48f915f7b8994cd45.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/13/1109671580_0:160:3072:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_23690fe7a9469f27a077a58657b30863.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Francisco Seco </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">叶卡捷琳娜布林诺娃</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_ekaterina_blinova/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a> <a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:e.blinova@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">土耳其总统雷杰普·塔伊普·埃尔多安 (Recep Tayyip Erdogan) 和他的竞争对手凯末尔·基利达罗格鲁 (Kemal Kilicdaroglu) 将于 5 月 28 日进行第二轮投票。两位候选人都有优点和缺点，因为土耳其人正在东西方之间取得平衡，人造卫星的对话者说。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">堪萨斯大学政治学副教授兼副主任 F. Michael Wuthrich 表示：“土耳其人的外交政策世界观受到国家长期以来不采取过于强烈的全球立场的倾向的影响，除非他们绝对如此。”全球与国际研究中心告诉人造卫星。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “因此，我认为 Turkiye 的地缘政治调整的任何变化都将是微小和渐进的，而且这种预期也与 Kilicdaroglu 的个性和性格相一致。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110405544" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230516/turkiye-will-continue-to-walk-tightrope-between-west-and-east-if-kilicdaroglu-wins-1110405544.html?share-block=1110408023" data-title="&quot;Therefore, I think any changes in Turkiye’s geopolitical alignment would be mostly minor and gradual, and such anticipation is also consistent with the personality and character of Kilicdaroglu in general.&quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这位教授表示，西方倾向于 Kilicdaroglu 并不是因为他与这些外国领导人之间有任何个人关系，而是因为这位反对派领导人的想法与美国和欧洲领导人产生了共鸣。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">决选将受到西方国家或欧盟成员国和北约成员国、美国，当然还有俄罗斯和中国的密切关注，“因为目前，全球范围内存在地缘政治分裂，”皮埃尔-伊曼纽尔·托曼 (Pierre-Emmanuel Thomann) 博士，他是地缘政治学教授，也是位于布鲁塞尔的国际组织欧洲大陆 (Eurocontinent) 的负责人。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “美国及其在欧洲的北约盟国正在重新集结，以支持美国的目标，反对俄罗斯和中国，也通过乌克兰的冲突，”托曼告诉卫星通讯社。 “所以欧亚分裂。实际上，如果土耳其改变路线，每个阵营，每个国家联盟都会喜欢它。美国和欧盟成员国，他们希望土耳其更加反对俄罗斯并停止从事商业活动与俄罗斯进行制裁，并对俄罗斯采取更强硬的态度，因为那是他们目前的对手。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110405544" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230516/turkiye-will-continue-to-walk-tightrope-between-west-and-east-if-kilicdaroglu-wins-1110405544.html?share-block=1110405548" data-title="&quot;The United States and its NATO allies in Europe are regrouping behind the American objectives and against Russia and China, also through the conflict in Ukraine,&quot; Thomann told Sputnik. &quot;So there is a Eurasian fragmentation. Actually each camp, each alliance of countries, would like it if Turkiye changed its course. The United States and the EU member states, they would like Turkiye to be more against Russia and to stop engaging in commerce with Russia, and to apply sanctions and also to be tougher on Russia, because that's their adversary at the moment.&quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h3"><h3 class="article__h2">基利达罗格鲁和埃尔多安</h3></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">埃尔多安以<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230515/turkiye-presidential-election-what-is-known-so-far-1110369436.html" target="_blank">49.5% 的选票在第一轮中脱颖而出，而他的主要竞争对手为 44.9%</a> 。西方媒体援引先前的调查指出，土耳其总统的表现好于预期。现在，媒体正在权衡埃尔多安和基利达罗格鲁<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230516/turkiye-election-shattered-the-illusion-that-erdogan-was-untouchable-1110392035.html" target="_blank">的当选胜算</a>。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Kilicdaroglu 最近向土耳其青年讲述了生活成本危机。他认为，回归西方式的正统货币政策以及与西方更紧密的联盟可以为该国挽救局面。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">与此同时，一些政治观察家注意到，尽管土耳其正遭受通货膨胀的折磨，但埃尔多安将国家安全利益置于经济挑战之上的计划奏效，引起了土耳其保守派和民族主义者的共鸣。一个明显的表现就是埃尔多安的联盟在议会中赢得多数席位。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p>另一方面，据一些评论员称，自 2010 年以来一直领导共和人民党 (CHP) 的基利达罗格鲁似乎犯了一个错误，他阻止了更年轻和受欢迎的党内成员投身其中。</p><p>此外，自 2010 年以来，Kilicdaroglu 的 CHP 在土耳其政治舞台上没有取得任何重大胜利。此外，他们认为 Kilicdaroglu 的六党国家联盟似乎并不那么团结，这唤起了土耳其人对前联合政府的政府危机的记忆。</p></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">还不清楚民族主义候选人希南·奥根的选民是否会支持基利达罗格鲁——奥根以 5.2% 的支持率位居第三。奥根周一对美国媒体表示，只有在竞争者排除对人民民主党 (HDP) 做出任何让步的情况下，他才会支持 Kilicdaroglu。早些时候有报道称，Kilicdaroglu 会见了 HDP 联合领导人，他们支持国家联盟。一些媒体将奥根的话视为对埃尔多安的潜在提振。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h3"><h3 class="article__h2"> Turkiye 的主要课程可能保持不变</h3></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">人造卫星的对话者一致认为，在当前的经济条件下，由于其独特的地缘政治地位，土耳其不能显着改变其已经在西方和东方之间分裂的路线。据观察人士称，无论谁获胜，安卡拉很可能会继续走钢丝。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “土耳其既是北约成员国，同时也是中东和欧亚大陆的一部分，”Thomann 解释说。 “土耳其想成为一个支点，在各个不同的圈子里获得优势。所以它会继续扮演北约成员国的角色，与美国一起在高加索和叙利亚制衡俄罗斯，并试图扩大其影响力。”在中亚。与此同时， <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230515/turkiye-wont-turn-its-back-on-russia-whoever-wins-presidential-runoff-1110386303.html" target="_blank">它仍将与俄罗斯进行谈判</a>（......）我们有一些共同的立场可以通过谈判来避免冲突，同时也可以提高我们自己的形象和力量，就像叙利亚的冲突一样。例如，Turkiye -叙利亚关系由俄罗斯监督，我认为土耳其不会改变这一点。他们将继续进行东西方定位。” </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110405544" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230516/turkiye-will-continue-to-walk-tightrope-between-west-and-east-if-kilicdaroglu-wins-1110405544.html?share-block=1110405559" data-title="&amp;quot;Turkiye is both a member of NATO and at the same time, it is a part of the Middle East and also Eurasia,&amp;quot; explained Thomann. &amp;quot;Turkiye wants to be a pivot and to gain an advantage in all different circles. So it will continue to play the role of a NATO-member state, with the US to counterbalance Russia in the Caucasus and in Syria and try to expand its influence in Central Asia. At the same time, it will still negotiate with Russia (…) We have some common positions to negotiate to avoid the conflict, but also to raise our own profile and power, like the conflict in Syria. For example, Turkiye-Syria relations are supervised by Russia, and I don&amp;#x27;t think Turkiye is on the way to changing that. They will continue to do both East and West positioning.&amp;quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">就他而言，Wuthrich 指出，在某种意义上，埃尔多安与基利达罗格鲁一样“西化”，尽管现任土耳其总统由于与俄罗斯和中国的关系而被描绘成东倾领导人： </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “我很难搞清楚你所说的‘西化’是什么意思，”Wuthrich 说。 “如果你的意思是从文化方面来说，最好回想一下哪位候选人将他们所有的孩子都送到了美国接受教育——比如埃尔多安。土耳其几十年来的对外政策使政党和领导人都倾向于亲美在土耳其的中间右翼，埃尔多安声称代表的意识形态遗产。这一传统的主要领导人门德列斯、德米雷尔和厄扎尔在他们的土耳其发展计划中非常明确地采用了“美国模式”。埃尔多安和他的政党开始具有强烈的美国和欧盟倾向，并提倡美国人（而不是法国）对世俗主义的理解，直到最近几年，埃尔多安才出现根据个人实用主义来确定关系。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110405544" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230516/turkiye-will-continue-to-walk-tightrope-between-west-and-east-if-kilicdaroglu-wins-1110405544.html?share-block=1110405561" data-title="&amp;quot;I have a hard time teasing out what you mean by &amp;#x27;westernized&amp;#x27;,&amp;quot; Wuthrich said. &amp;quot;If you mean that from a cultural aspect, it might be good to recall which of the candidates sent all their children to the United States for education—i.e. Erdogan. Decades of Turkish foreign approaches have situated pro-US tendencies with the parties and leaders on the center right in Turkey, the ideological legacy of which Erdogan claims to represent. Menderes, Demirel and Ozal, the main leaders of this tradition, very explicitly adopted the &amp;#x27;American model&amp;#x27; in their plans for Turkey’s development. Erdogan and his party started with a strong US and EU slant and advocated for an American (rather than French) understanding of secularism, and it has only been in recent years that Erdogan has appeared to determine relations based on personal pragmatism."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “在土耳其的传统意识形态基础上，欧亚主义一直是土耳其左翼和土耳其民族主义极右翼中许多人的愿景。Kilicdaroglu 的意识形态传统可能比美国更重视欧洲的做法，特别是在北欧和西欧。埃尔多安远比 Kilicdaroglu 更符合美国的经济自由主义，”Wuthrich 总结道。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 16 May 2023 21:57:24 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230516/turkiye-will-continue-to-walk-tightrope-between-west-and-east-if-kilicdaroglu-wins-1110405544.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230516/turkiye-will-continue-to-walk-tightrope-between-west-and-east-if-kilicdaroglu-wins-1110405544.html<category>分析</category><category>雷杰普·塔伊普·埃尔多安</category><category>凯末尔·基利达罗格鲁</category><category>思南奥根</category><category>突厥耶</category><category>俄罗斯</category><category>东方</category><category>北约</category><category>欧盟 (EU)</category><category>观点</category><category>我们</category><category>欧洲</category><category>中东</category></item></channel></rss>